@teng-li
Really thanks. The functions, like torch.scatter_add_(), torch.gather(), need the LongTensor as their indexes, so I init these long tensors first in the class __init__.
I init them as Float Tensor first, when passing them into functions as the indexes, I convert their types as LongTensor. It should work well.

body:
@teng-li 
Really thanks. The functions, like `torch.scatter_add_()`, `torch.gather()`, need the `LongTensor` as their indexes, so I init these long tensors first in the `class __init__`. 

I init them as Float Tensor first, when passing them into functions as the indexes, I convert their types as LongTensor. It should work well.
